{
  "texts": [
    "These individual clusters also form larger regional superclusters.",
    "More specifically, continental European countries form a large, distinct cluster.",
    "The United States and Canada form another, with the United Kingdom located between this North American group and the continental European cluster.",
    "Puerto Rico and Mexico form their own cluster, positioned near the one containing the United States and Canada.Likewise, the plot for the category-based sample (Fig. 8.bottom) reveals logical groupings based on business type.",
    "For instance, drug stores and grocery stores are in close proximity, an intuitive finding that reflects the modern retail strategy where grocery stores incorporate pharmacies and drug stores expand their food and household staple selections."
  ]
}